# [DOMAIN NAME] - Handoff

> The relay baton. Written at the end of every session. Read at the start of the next one.
>
> Purpose: give the next session everything it needs to pick up immediately,
> without relying on conversation history (which doesn't persist).
>
> Each session's handoff goes under its own date header. Keep the last 3-5 sessions.
> Older entries can be deleted - they're historical at that point and belong in the Log.

---

## [YYYY-MM-DD] - Session Handoff

### What Was Done
- [Specific thing completed]
- [Specific thing completed]
- [Include enough detail that the next session doesn't need to re-investigate]

### In Progress
- [Task that's started but not finished]
  - Current state: [where it stands]
  - Next action: [what needs to happen next]

### Blocked
- [Task that can't proceed]
  - Blocked by: [what's in the way]
  - Waiting on: [person / decision / access / deadline]

### Context for Next Session
- [Anything the next session should know that isn't obvious from the Queue or files]
- [Decisions made and why]
- [Important file paths or IDs]
- [Things to watch out for]

